[14:23:18] {"event": "tool_result", "tool": "view", "is_error": false, "result": {"status": "success", "file": "/Users/virginia.zambudio/PlaywrightAutomation/artifacts/outputs/quality-engineering-web-automation/validated-test-cases/DISCOVERY-SPEC-DISCOVERY-PLI-20260715.md", "content": "1: # DISCOVERY-SPEC-DISCOVERY-PLI-20260715\n2: \n3: ## Session\n4: - **Session ID:** DISCOVERY-PLI-20260715\n5: - **Date:** 2026-07-15\n6: - **Application:** London Drugs UAT — https://london-drugs-uat-origin.kibology.us/\n7: - **Scope:** Fix 6 failing tests via live selector discovery and timing analysis\n8: \n9: ---\n10: \n11: ## Findings — Selector Validation\n12: \n13: ### TC-83232 — Newsletter Signup (home-page.spec.ts)\n14: \n15: | Element | Selector | Confirmed |\n16: |---|---|---|\n17: | Email input | `div.bg-primary input[type=\"email\"]` | ✓ visible after scroll |\n18: | Submit button | `div.bg-primary button[type=\"submit\"]` (hasText `/sign up/i`) | ✓ present, **covered** by layout `div` |\n19: \n20: **Root causes identified:**\n21: 1. **(Chromium/Edge — original)** `waitFor({ state: 'visible', timeout: 30_000 })` at old line 414 was too short; fixed in working tree with 45s + retry loop.\n22: 2. **(Edge — new)** `newsletterSubmitButton.click()` silently failed because a layout `div` covered the button on Edge. Fix: `click({ force: true })`.\n23: \n24: **Live DOM evidence:**\n25: ```\n26: button text: \"SIGN UP\"\n27: button class: \"border-white-600 flex h-10 items-center justify-center rounded-none border-2 p-3\"\n28: covered by: DIV class=\"mx-auto hidden max-w-[1272px] flex-row items-center justify-between px-2 py-3 lg\"\n29: ```\n30: \n31: ---\n32: \n33: ### TC-83240 — Login (LoginPage.ts)\n34: \n35: | Element | Selector | Confirmed |\n36: |---|---|---|\n37: | Email input | `input[name=\"email\"][type=\"email\"]` | ✓ visible on `/auth/login` |\n38: | Password input | `input[name=\"password\"][type=\"password\"]` | ✓ |\n39: | Login button | `button[type=\"submit\"]` hasText `/login/i` | ✓ |\n40: \n41: **Root cause:**\n42: - **(Chromium — original)** Old code navigated to `/myaccount` (redirect chain); old timeout was 15s.\n43: - **(Edge — new)** After fixing to `/auth/login`, Edge got stuck on \"Loading...\" spinner. `BasePage.navigate()` (which calls `dismissLoadingIfStuck()` + `waitForAppShell()`) resolves the stuck state; added extra `body.click({ force: true })` before waiting for email input.\n44: \n45: ---\n46: \n47: ### TC-83238 — In-Store Pickup Store Selector (ProductDetailPage.ts)\n48: \n49: | Element | Selector | Confirmed |\n50: |---|---|---|\n51: | In-store pickup radio | `input[aria-label=\"Product Ship to Store Pickup Fulfillment Type\"]` | ✓ |\n52: | \"Set your store\" link | `p.cursor-pointer.text-primary` hasText `/set your store/i` | ✓ class: `mr-1 cursor-pointer text-primary underline` |\n53: | \"Check Availability\" link | `p.cursor-pointer` hasText `/check availability at other stores/i` | ✓ |\n54: | Store selector dialog | `dialog#store-selector` | ✓ |\n55: | Search input | `dialog#store-selector input[name=\"searchTerm\"]` | ✓ |\n56: | Search button | `dialog#store-selector button.primary-button` (first) | ✓ text: \"SEARCH STORES\" |\n57: | First Set Store button | `dialog#store-selector button.primary-button` (nth 1) | ✓ text: \"Set Store\" |\n58: \n59: **Root cause (Firefox/WebKit):**\n60: 1. **(Original)** Old `openStoreSelectorDialog` used single 15s wait → fixed with fallback logic in working tree.\n61: 2. **(New — after phase 1 fix)** `searchStores()` had `firstSetStoreButton.waitFor({ timeout: 15_000 })`. Firefox/WebKit store search API responses took >15s. Fix: increased to 30s.\n62: \n63: ---\n64: \n65: ## Wait Strategy Inventory\n66: \n67: | Flow | Strategy |\n68: |---|---|\n69: | Newsletter section appears | `scrollTo(document.body.scrollHeight)` × 2, retry loop (15×1s), `scrollIntoViewIfNeeded`, final `waitFor(45s)` |\n70: | Newsletter button | `click({ force: true })` to bypass overlay |\n71: | Login form | `BasePage.navigate()` + `networkidle(20s)` + `body.click({force})` + `waitFor(45s)` |\n72: | Store selector opens | `scrollIntoViewIfNeeded` + 2.5s wait + try/catch 5s → fallback 15s |\n73: | Store search results | `waitFor({ timeout: 30_000 })` on first Set Store button |\n74: \n75: ---\n76: \n77: ## Open Questions\n78: \n79: | # | Question | Impact |\n80: |---|---|---|\n81: | OQ-001 | TC-83232 test email `test_qa_automation@example.com` — if already registered, UAT may redirect differently | Could cause redirect mismatch |\n82: | OQ-002 | TC-83238 product found via \"vitamins\" search varies; product must support in-store pickup | If product lacks ISP, test will fail |"}}
[14:23:18] {"event": "tool_call", "tool": "view", "args": {"file_path": "/Users/virginia.zambudio/PlaywrightAutomation/artifacts/outputs/quality-engineering-web-automation/framework-architecture/FRAMEWORK-SPEC-FRAMEWORK-PLAYWRIGHTAUTOMATION-20260715.md", "limit": 100}}
[14:23:18] {"event": "tool_result", "tool": "view", "is_error": false, "result": {"status": "success", "file": "/Users/virginia.zambudio/PlaywrightAutomation/artifacts/outputs/quality-engineering-web-automation/framework-architecture/FRAMEWORK-SPEC-FRAMEWORK-PLAYWRIGHTAUTOMATION-20260715.md", "content": "1: # FRAMEWORK-SPEC-FRAMEWORK-PLAYWRIGHTAUTOMATION-20260715\n2: \n3: **Version:** 1.0.0  \n4: **Session ID:** FRAMEWORK-PLAYWRIGHTAUTOMATION-20260715  \n5: **Scenario:** 2 — First Interaction with Existing Framework  \n6: **Generated:** 2026-07-15  \n7: **Project:** PlaywrightAutomation — London Drugs UAT Regression Suite\n8: \n9: ---\n10: \n11: ## 1. Project Overview\n12: \n13: | Field | Value |\n14: |---|---|\n15: | Project name | playwrightautomation |\n16: | Repository path | `/Users/virginia.zambudio/PlaywrightAutomation` |\n17: | Environment under test | `https://london-drugs-uat-origin.kibology.us/` |\n18: | Framework type | Playwright + TypeScript, Page Object Model |\n19: | Test runner | `@playwright/test` v1.61.x |\n20: | TypeScript version | 6.x |\n21: | Node module format | CommonJS |\n22: | CI system | GitHub Actions (`.github/workflows/playwright.yml`, `regression.yml`) |\n23: \n24: **Application profile:**  \n25: London Drugs e-commerce (Next.js + Builder.io). Characterized by slow React hydration on UAT (15–45 s spinners), Builder.io lazy-rendered sections (intersection-observer gated), geolocation-driven store pre-selection, and cross-domain sort/filter redirects to `www.londondrugs.com`.\n26: \n27: ---\n28: \n29: ## 2. Technology Stack\n30: \n31: | Layer | Technology | Version |\n32: |---|---|---|\n33: | Test framework | `@playwright/test` | ^1.61.0 |\n34: | Language | TypeScript | ^6.0.3 |\n35: | Node types | `@types/node` | ^25.9.4 |\n36: | Browsers | Chromium, Firefox, WebKit, Edge (msedge) | Playwright-bundled |\n37: | Build/run | `npx playwright test` | — |\n38: | Reporting | JUnit XML + Playwright HTML reporter | built-in |\n39: | CI | GitHub Actions | — |\n40: \n41: **Notable runtime settings (playwright.config.ts):**\n42: - `baseURL`: `https://london-drugs-uat-origin.kibology.us/` (overridable via `BASE_URL` env var)\n43: - `locale`: `en-CA`\n44: - `geolocation`: Vancouver BC `{lat: 49.2827, lng: -123.1207}` — triggers store pre-selection on Firefox/WebKit\n45: - `permissions`: `['geolocation']`\n46: - `headless`: true in CI, false locally\n47: - `slowMo`: 800 ms locally, 0 in CI\n48: - `retries`: 2 in CI, 0 locally\n49: - `workers`: 1 in CI (serial), unlimited locally\n50: - `trace`: off (ZIP stream corruption workaround for Playwright 1.61)\n51: - `screenshot`: off (custom evidence helper handles this)\n52: - Global timeout: 60 000 ms (individual tests may override with `test.setTimeout()`)\n53: \n54: ---\n55: \n56: ## 3. Component Catalog\n57: \n58: ### 3.1 Page Objects (`pages/`)\n59: \n60: | Class | File | Responsibility |\n61: |---|---|---|\n62: | `BasePage` | `BasePage.ts` | Base class: `navigate()`, `dismissLoadingIfStuck()`, `waitForAppShell()`. Handles Next.js/Builder.io hydration stalls via body-click. |\n63: | `HomePage` | `HomePage.ts` | Home page: logo, search input, mini cart, mega menu, header nav links (Deals, Services, Flyers, Gift Registry), footer newsletter signup. |\n64: | `LoginPage` | `LoginPage.ts` | Login form: email/password inputs, submit button. `login()` navigates directly to `/auth/login` (skips `/myaccount` redirect round-trip). |\n65: | `ProductDetailPage` | `ProductDetailPage.ts` | PDP: breadcrumbs, price, availability, fulfillment radios, store selector dialog, delivery postal code modal, Add to Cart, mini cart badge, wishlist button. |\n66: | `SearchResultsPage` | `SearchResultsPage.ts` | PLP/search: filter, sort, product card interactions. |\n67: | `StoreLocatorPage` | `StoreLocatorPage.ts` | Store locator page interactions. |\n68: \n69: **BasePage contract:**\n70: - `navigate(url)` — `goto()` + `domcontentloaded` + `dismissLoadingIfStuck()` + `waitForAppShell()`\n71: - `dismissLoadingIfStuck()` — waits for `load` (15 s); if timeout, force-clicks body + waits `domcontentloaded`\n72: - `waitForAppShell()` — waits for `header` to be visible (20 s); on failure force-clicks body\n73: \n74: ### 3.2 Test Specs (`tests/`)\n75: \n76: | File | Test IDs covered |\n77: |---|---|\n78: | `home-page.spec.ts` | TC-83225, TC-83226, TC-83228, TC-83229, TC-83230, TC-83231, TC-83232 |\n79: | `pdp.spec.ts` | TC-83235, TC-83236, TC-83237, TC-83238, TC-83239, TC-83240 |\n80: | `plp.spec.ts` | FTC_02_01_x, FTC_02_02_x (PLP filter/sort scenarios) |\n81: \n82: All specs use `test.afterEach` to call `takeEvidenceScreenshot()` on failure.\n83: \n84: ### 3.3 Helpers (`helpers/`)\n85: \n86: | Helper | File | Responsibility |\n87: |---|---|---|\n88: | Evidence screenshots | `evidence.ts` | Captures full-page PNG on test failure; saves to `artifacts/outputs/` with `{TC-ID}_{timestamp}.png` naming. |\n89: | Page load unblocking | `page-load.ts` | `simulateBodyClickToUnblock()` — thin wrapper for the body-click hydration pattern. |\n90: | API interceptor | `apiInterceptor.ts` | `interceptSearchApi()`, `waitForFilterApiCall()`, `interceptAndAbortSortRedirect()` / `interceptAndAbortFilterRedirect()` — handles UAT search API interception and production-domain redirect abortion. |\n91: \n92: ### 3.4 Test Data (`test-data/`)\n93: \n94: | File | Covers |\n95: |---|---|\n96: | `home-page.data.ts` | URLs, logo assertions, search terms, mini cart data, header nav hrefs, newsletter email + expected redirect pattern |\n97: | `pdp.data.ts` | PDP URLs, postal code `V6B 1A1`, auth credentials (from env vars `TEST_USER_EMAIL` / `TEST_USER_PASSWORD`) |\n98: | `plp.data.ts` | Filter/sort data, URL params for sort verification |\n99: \n100: ### 3.5 CI Workflows (`.github/workflows/`)"}}
[14:23:22] {"event": "tool_call", "tool": "view", "args": {"file_path": "/Users/virginia.zambudio/PlaywrightAutomation/artifacts/outputs/quality-engineering-web-automation/framework-architecture/FRAMEWORK-SPEC-FRAMEWORK-PLAYWRIGHTAUTOMATION-20260715.md", "offset": 100, "limit": 200}}
[14:23:22] {"event": "tool_result", "tool": "view", "is_error": false, "result": {"status": "success", "file": "/Users/virginia.zambudio/PlaywrightAutomation/artifacts/outputs/quality-engineering-web-automation/framework-architecture/FRAMEWORK-SPEC-FRAMEWORK-PLAYWRIGHTAUTOMATION-20260715.md", "content": "100: ### 3.5 CI Workflows (`.github/workflows/`)\n101: \n102: | File | Trigger | Purpose |\n103: |---|---|---|\n104: | `playwright.yml` | Push/PR | Full regression run on all 4 browsers |\n105: | `regression.yml` | Schedule/manual | Scheduled regression with JUnit XML artifact upload |\n106: \n107: ---\n108: \n109: ## 4. Architecture Decisions\n110: \n111: | ID | Decision | Rationale |\n112: |---|---|---|\n113: | AD-01 | Page Object Model (POM) | Encapsulates selectors and interactions; isolates test logic from DOM changes. |\n114: | AD-02 | `BasePage` hydration pattern | Next.js + Builder.io UAT origin requires body-click + header wait after every navigation to unblock hydration stalls. Centralized in `BasePage` for DRY reuse. |\n115: | AD-03 | Navigate to `/auth/login` directly | Bypasses `/myaccount` → `/auth/login` redirect round-trip; reduces flakiness on slow UAT origin (saves ~5–10 s, avoids double-navigation spinner). |\n116: | AD-04 | Geolocation set to Vancouver | Ensures consistent locale/store availability behavior across all test runs. Side effect: Firefox/WebKit may auto-select a store, requiring fallback logic in store selector interactions. |\n117: | AD-05 | `interceptAndAbortSortRedirect` | UAT sort/filter actions redirect to `www.londondrugs.com`. Route interception aborts the redirect so assertions remain on UAT origin. |\n118: | AD-06 | Custom evidence screenshots (off by default) | `screenshot: 'off'` in config; `evidence.ts` captures only on failure with deterministic filename. Avoids Playwright ZIP stream corruption bug (v1.61). |\n119: | AD-07 | `trace: 'off'` | Playwright 1.61 ZIP stream corruption bug makes traces unreliable; disabled until upstream fix. |\n120: | AD-08 | 4-browser matrix (Chromium, Firefox, WebKit, Edge) | London Drugs has a diverse user agent base; cross-browser coverage catches browser-specific rendering/geolocation differences. |\n121: | AD-09 | Edge via `msedge` channel | Added 2026-07-14; requires separate `npx playwright install msedge` step in CI (not included in `--with-deps`). |\n122: | AD-10 | `openStoreSelectorDialog()` dual-state fallback | Firefox/WebKit auto-select store via geolocation, replacing \"Set your store\" with \"Check availability at other stores\". Method tries \"Set your store\" (5 s) then falls back to \"Check availability\" (15 s). |\n123: | AD-11 | Builder.io newsletter retry loop | Newsletter section is intersection-observer gated. Scroll + retry loop (15 attempts × 1 s) + 45 s final `waitFor` handles slow UAT Builder.io rendering. |\n124: \n125: ---\n126: \n127: ## 5. Configuration Strategy\n128: \n129: ### 5.1 Environment Variables\n130: \n131: | Variable | Usage | Default |\n132: |---|---|---|\n133: | `BASE_URL` | Overrides `playwright.config.ts` `baseURL` | `https://london-drugs-uat-origin.kibology.us/` |\n134: | `CI` | Enables CI mode (headless, no slowMo, 2 retries, 1 worker) | unset (local) |\n135: | `TEST_USER_EMAIL` | Authenticated test user email (TC-83240) | Must be set |\n136: | `TEST_USER_PASSWORD` | Authenticated test user password (TC-83240) | Must be set |\n137: \n138: ### 5.2 Timeout Hierarchy\n139: \n140: | Level | Timeout | Source |\n141: |---|---|---|\n142: | Global test timeout | 60 000 ms | `playwright.config.ts` |\n143: | TC-83232 override | 180 000 ms | `test.setTimeout(180_000)` in spec |\n144: | App shell hydration | 20 000 ms | `BasePage.waitForAppShell()` |\n145: | Load state | 15 000 ms | `BasePage.dismissLoadingIfStuck()` |\n146: | Login email input | 45 000 ms | `LoginPage.login()` |\n147: | Newsletter `waitFor` | 45 000 ms | `home-page.spec.ts` TC-83232 |\n148: | Store selector fallback | 15 000 ms | `ProductDetailPage.openStoreSelectorDialog()` |\n149: | Store search results | 30 000 ms | `ProductDetailPage.searchStores()` |\n150: | Add to Cart confirmation | 20 000 ms | `ProductDetailPage.addToCart()` |\n151: \n152: ---\n153: \n154: ## 6. Known Issues & Fixes Applied (2026-07-15)\n155: \n156: The following failures from the previous CI run were diagnosed and fixed:\n157: \n158: ### F-01: TC-83232 Newsletter Timeout (Chromium, Edge)\n159: - **Root cause:** Old code had `waitFor({ timeout: 30_000 })` with no retry loop; Builder.io section required longer wait and scroll trigger.\n160: - **Fix:** Added 15-iteration scroll retry loop + 45 s final `waitFor`. Selector `div.bg-primary input[type=\"email\"]` confirmed valid via browser inspection.\n161: - **File:** `tests/home-page.spec.ts`\n162: \n163: ### F-02: TC-83240 Login Timeout (Chromium, Edge)\n164: - **Root cause:** Old code navigated to `/myaccount` with 15 s timeout; `/myaccount` triggers redirect to `/auth/login`, adding a round-trip + double spinner.\n165: - **Fix:** Navigate directly to `/auth/login` + `networkidle` wait + body click + 45 s `waitFor`. Selector `input[name=\"email\"][type=\"email\"]` confirmed valid via browser inspection.\n166: - **File:** `pages/LoginPage.ts`\n167: \n168: ### F-03: TC-83238 Store Selector Timeout (Firefox, WebKit)\n169: - **Root cause:** Geolocation pre-selects Vancouver store on Firefox/WebKit, hiding \"Set your store\" link. Old code waited 15 s for that specific locator with no fallback.\n170: - **Fix:** `openStoreSelectorDialog()` now: scrolls fulfillment radio into view → waits 2.5 s → tries \"Set your store\" (5 s try/catch) → falls back to \"Check availability at other stores\" (15 s).\n171: - **File:** `pages/ProductDetailPage.ts`\n172: \n173: ---\n174: \n175: ## 7. Code Review Checklist\n176: \n177: ### Selectors\n178: - [x] All selectors use stable attributes (`aria-label`, `name`, `type`, `data-*`) or scoped class+tag combinations\n179: - [x] No bare class selectors on dynamically-generated Tailwind classes\n180: - [x] `p.cursor-pointer.text-primary` is scoped by `.filter({ hasText: ... })` to avoid ambiguity\n181: - [x] Newsletter input scoped to parent `div.bg-primary` to avoid matching other email inputs\n182: \n183: ### Timing & Stability\n184: - [x] No bare `waitForTimeout` used as primary wait (used only as hydration nudge after scroll)\n185: - [x] All `waitFor({ state: 'visible' })` have explicit timeout values matching the timeout hierarchy\n186: - [x] Login navigates to `/auth/login` directly (no redirect round-trip)\n187: - [x] `openStoreSelectorDialog()` has dual-state fallback for geolocation pre-selection\n188: - [x] `networkidle` waits use `.catch(() => {})` to prevent test failure on busy UAT pages\n189: \n190: ### API Interception\n191: - [x] `interceptAndAbortSortRedirect` registered before sort/filter action, not after\n192: - [x] `interceptSearchApi` uses `page.unroute()` after first match to avoid leaking route handlers\n193: \n194: ### Evidence & Reporting\n195: - [x] `takeEvidenceScreenshot` called in `afterEach` on all spec files\n196: - [x] Evidence files saved to `artifacts/outputs/` with deterministic `{TC-ID}_{timestamp}.png` naming\n197: - [x] JUnit XML output (`results.xml`) consumed by ADO publish script\n198: \n199: ### Open Items\n200: - [ ] OQ-01: Sort/filter on UAT may redirect to `www.londondrugs.com`. `interceptAndAbortSortRedirect` is the current workaround; needs re-validation if UAT is promoted.\n201: - [ ] OQ-02: `TEST_USER_EMAIL` / `TEST_USER_PASSWORD` must be set as GitHub Actions secrets for TC-83240 to pass in CI.\n202: - [ ] OQ-03: Edge (`msedge`) requires separate `npx playwright install msedge` step in CI pipeline — not covered by `--with-deps`.\n203: \n204: ---\n205: \n206: ## 8. Architecture Diagram (Logical)\n207: \n208: ```\n209: tests/\n210:   home-page.spec.ts   → HomePage, StoreLocatorPage, evidence.ts\n211:   pdp.spec.ts         → HomePage, LoginPage, ProductDetailPage, SearchResultsPage, evidence.ts, apiInterceptor.ts\n212:   plp.spec.ts         → SearchResultsPage, evidence.ts, apiInterceptor.ts\n213: \n214: pages/\n215:   BasePage.ts         ← extended by all page objects\n216:   HomePage.ts\n217:   LoginPage.ts\n218:   ProductDetailPage.ts\n219:   SearchResultsPage.ts\n220:   StoreLocatorPage.ts\n221: \n222: helpers/\n223:   evidence.ts         ← afterEach screenshot on failure\n224:   page-load.ts        ← simulateBodyClickToUnblock()\n225:   apiInterceptor.ts   ← interceptSearchApi, interceptAndAbortSortRedirect\n226: \n227: test-data/\n228:   home-page.data.ts\n229:   pdp.data.ts\n230:   plp.data.ts\n231: \n232: playwright.config.ts  ← 4-browser matrix, baseURL, geolocation, timeouts\n233: ```"}}
